external_knowledge:
- The difference between reported and calculated end balances can indicate potential financial irregularities or errors in accounting; 
- A discrepancy greater than 100,000 may signify a significant issue that needs attention; 
- The top three reports per organization provide a focused view of the most critical discrepancies, allowing for targeted investigation and resolution.

sql:
SELECT report_id, difference
FROM financial_reports
WHERE ABS(difference) > 10000;

SELECT analyst_id, COUNT(*) AS analysis_count
FROM financial_analysis
GROUP BY analyst_id;
